<task id="003" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-03 Add Persona Resolution Methods to `IScopeResolverService` (Pillar 1)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed>2026-06-07</completed>
    <completion-notes>
Implemented R6 Pillar 1 D-A-03 persona resolution methods following Q1 most-specific-wins
precedence (playbook-attached > tenant CUST- > global SYS-). Reused the canonical
DataverseHttpServiceBase pattern from AnalysisActionService/Skill/Knowledge/Tool.

Files modified:
  - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IScopeResolverService.cs (+62 lines):
    added ResolvePersonaForChatAsync + GetEffectivePersonaAsync interface methods
    with full XML docs explaining FR-03/FR-04/NFR-01/NFR-14 bindings.
  - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisPersonaService.cs (+140 lines):
    extended task 002's skeleton with ResolvePersonaForChatAsync (throws on missing SYS-
    default per FR-04) + GetEffectivePersonaAsync (returns null on full miss) +
    QueryFirstByScopeTypeAsync helper. Three precedence layers query Dataverse with explicit
    sprk_scopetype + NFR-14 SYS-/CUST- prefix filters as defense-in-depth.
  - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ScopeResolverService.cs (modified):
    replaced task 002's NotImplementedException stubs (lines 390-404) with delegating calls
    to _personaService.
  - tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/PersonaResolutionTests.cs (NEW, 409 lines):
    13 unit tests covering: no overrides → SYS- default (FR-04); tenant override wins
    (FR-03); playbook override wins over tenant + SYS- (FR-03); fall-through when
    playbook bound but missing; NFR-14 query filter URL inspection (CUST- + SYS- prefix);
    no-playbookId skips playbook query; null at every layer returns null; throws on no
    SYS- default; argument validation (blank + null tenantId). All 13 PASSED in 29 ms.

DI: AnalysisPersonaService already registered by task 002 in AnalysisServicesModule
    (services.AddHttpClient&lt;AnalysisPersonaService&gt;()), so no DI changes needed
    in this task.

Parallel coordination with task 002 (ListPersonasAsync endpoint owner): clean — task 002
added the DTO (AnalysisPersona record + PersonaScopeType enum), ListPersonasAsync interface
method + AnalysisPersonaService skeleton + DI registration + ScopeResolverService stubs.
Task 003 added the resolver interface methods + the resolver implementations + tests.
Zero file-overlap on method signatures.

Build: dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -c Release → 0 errors, 16 warnings
(baseline). Tests: 13/13 PASSED.

BFF publish-size: compressed 45.50 MB vs 45.65 MB baseline (CLAUDE.md 2026-05-26) =
−0.15 MB delta. Well under R6 +5 MB total budget per NFR-02; ceiling 60 MB unaffected.

Quality gates (Step 9.5):
  - code-review: PASS (0 critical, 0 warning, 0 suggestion, 0 AI smells)
  - adr-check: PASS (17 ADRs/NFRs verified compliant; ADR-010/-013/-014/NFR-01/NFR-14
    explicitly checked; BFF §10 hygiene checklist complete with placement justification
    + facade-boundary verification)

Downstream: task 005 (SprkChatAgentFactory wiring) can now call
ScopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, playbookId, ct) to replace the
hardcoded BuildDefaultSystemPrompt() call. Pending tasks 002 (endpoint) + 004 (SYS- seed
row) are parallel siblings — Wave A-G1 main session reconciles after all three close.
